Excess requirements for public procurement applications will be excluded by law
The law may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session, the state Dumas plan to consider in the second reading a bill setting out the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, the participants of which can be only small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The bill was developed in accordance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Entrepreneurship in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to request as part of the application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also - about the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" framework regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, registration and composition of the application for participation in the purchase are established by customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, extracts, the date of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable with the deadline for submitting applications, which leads to the impossibility of participating in such a purchase and reducing the number of participants in the purchase," the explanation of the bill reads.
The new draft law provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to request as part of the application from procurement participants who are small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," the explanatory note says.
