The authorities of the Moscow region told about the fate of closed landfills
In the suburbs continue to close landfills of solid household waste.
This year, the authorities promise to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills are being modernized into modern recycling complexes.
But this option is not possible for every landfill - many of them are overgrown with dense residential buildings.
After the landfill is closed, it gets up for recultivation - the body of the landfill is covered with soils, degassing and infiltration systems are installed.
This allows you to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not emit an odor, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill remains to rise useless pile among the surrounding residential buildings.
Why not make something useful out of it?
For example, in Ruza, where the reclamation of the Annino training ground was completed the other day, the authorities are considering the option of making a pile of ski slopes.
This landfill, which operated from 1976 to 2016, has grown so that it has gone beyond the boundaries of the land allocated for it.
Therefore, during the reclamation, it was necessary to buy out neighboring areas, de facto already clogged with garbage for a long time.
“Some time will pass, the landfill will “settle down”, gain a fortress, and we will think what can be done to make it useful.
Directly in the eyes is a ski resort," - told reporters the head of the Ruz district Nikolai Parfenov.
Two landfills will become sites for the production of renewable energy sources
