Timokhovo will produce 72.5 million kilowatt-hours and will continue to operate as a waste processing complex.
And a museum can be set up at the Balashikha Kuchino training ground, which was closed after residents’ complaints on the Direct Line with the country’s president.
"There was such an idea - to create a museum of reclamation of landfills near Moscow," - said Deputy Prime Minister - Minister of Ecology and Environmental Management of the region Dmitry Kurakin.
